<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In Zend\Module\ConfigListener, the only method to override global modules configuration is :</p>

<p>public function addConfigGlobPath($globPath)</p>

<p>But the override is based on the glob() php function :</p>

<p>-&gt; $config = ConfigFactory::fromFiles(glob($globPath, GLOB_BRACE))</p>

<p>The performance are slow with that. Why not a possibility to configure override with a static name, like addConfigGlobalFile('config/static/global.config.php') ?</p>

    </div>
</div>

